nts1.n: SOUNDS ON SCREEN: BRIAN DE PALMA (R)
nts1.d:
Scores, needle drops and iconic moments from the filmography of Brian De Palma - once a star of the New Hollywood movement of the 60s and 70s, De Palma famously admitted he wished to become the "American Godard". His style is broad, and allusive to his cinematic heroes – Godard, Hitchcock, Antonioni – creating cult classic and popcorn blockbusters alike, with the patchy critical reception that only a fiercely independent creative spirit could earn. 
Selected and mixed by Florence Scott-Anderton.

High Jazz* is an independent record label specializing in 70s & 80s soul, jazz & funk. ill Dubio takes the reigns for the monthly High Jazz* show rustling up an hour of choice selections on a Wednesday.

nts1.n: PANORAMA YEREVAN - ARMENIAN WOMEN IN MUSIC SPECIAL (R)
nts1.d: Lucia Kagramanayn celebrates Armenian female talent in music across time, genres, generations and diaspora communities featuring Armenian women in music from the ancient times to the present day.
Vinyl only selections from TOPS’ personal collections

nts1.n: RICH & JOHNNY'S INZANE MICHIGAN - BLUEJOHN FALL SPECIAL (R)
nts1.d: Join John Olson (aka Inzane Johnny, of Wolf Eyes) and music writer Rich Tupica as they mine deep into Michigan's wilderness of sounds. No private press rarity is off limits: soul, gospel, oddities, punk, experimental, rockabilly, and garage rock. It's all unearthed. Strap in for an insanely bizarre ride across the Great Lakes State.

Known for his films in post dictatorship South Korea which focus on the repressive climate of South Korea,  often through the perspective of working class Koreans. Memory, Tragedy & Trauma are themes often present in his films.This sounds on screen takes an hour of music from the films of South Korean director Lee-Chang Dong.
Guitar music, electronic musings and heady explorations with Baba Stiltz.

West Coast Fog with Erik Bluhm, broadcasts monthly from far-flung natural environments, bringing along site specific, privately released meditational music from past decades for a deeply involved sensory experience.

nts1.n: NTS GUIDE TO: ACOUSTIC COUNTRY BLUES -(R)
nts1.d: Stripped back acoustic blues from Mississippi John Hurt, Skip James, Lightnin Hopkins and more, selected by NTS.

Up with the Lark! Launette takes time out from her day job as a chocolatier to play from her treasured vinyl collection. She will also be joined from time to time by carefully chosen guests. Happy Sunday.
NYC based selector Fitzum digs through his personal history, playing an hour of classic Eritrean instrumental tracks, dating from 1985 to the mid-2000s.

nts2.d: For me, peace is synonymous with home — a corner of the world that we carve out and enrich with every facet of our identity. Here I offer up a set of tracks to play when you want to feel the walls pulsing with sweet, sweet soul.

nts2.n: Where Earth Meets Sky w/ Chi-Chi Usagi
nts2.d: I’m coming out from two of the toughest years of my life, and the music you are about to hear is what saved me. This mix features the song I walked down the aisle to at my wedding a few months before my life was flipped upside down, songs that held me through lonely nights dealing with withdrawals from an addiction I’d held onto for 10 years, songs that comforted me when I was kicked out of my career, songs that I danced on the roof to in the rain during the last nights in my home, Brooklyn, NY. All of this music has held me through moments that tested my willpower. The love that I have for myself and the love that I have for God is what got me through it all. May this little snippet of my peace touch something within you.

From Coal Creek Canyon, just miles from the former Rocky Flats nuclear site in Colorado, comes songs of peace, love and protest - a soundtrack for reflection, resilience, and the fight for a safer world.

nts2.n: Autostereo w/ Ben Schwartz: Protect And Survive
nts2.d: The specter of nuclear war has produced decades of impassioned, angry, and sometimes blackly comic music. With their depictions of devastation and aftermath, these songs have lost none of their power or relevancy and continue to serve as potent warnings against nuclear proliferation. Ban the Bomb!

nts2.n: THE GARDEN WITHIN W/ JOLIE ASUNCION
nts2.d: This mix is a collection is some of my favorite psychedelic tracks from the 60s and 70s, celebrating themes of peace, nature, love, and unity in times when the world needs them most.

Estas son canciones que hablan de paz, inspiran paz, son letras que buscan de la libertad, la hermandad y la hablan sobre la sociedad en que vivimos donde muchas veces lamentablemente no nos dejan vivir en paz.

nts2.n: Peace is Being Present W/ Eli
nts2.d:
To me, peace in a world overflowing with information is simply being present. It’s the continuous feeling of a moment you wish would never end. 
When you exist only there, untouched by the past, unburdened by the future

Im sitting on a bus looking out the window observing the movement all around me while music playing in my headphones transports me into an introspective state of mystery & wonder. Perhaps im daydreaming about my first love to some nostalgic dark ambient breakbeats or maybe im trying to grasp the concept of time to some soft 70s bossa nova. That’s peace for me.

nts2.n: Regions of Peace w/ steven seven seven
nts2.d:
A mix that embraces music from different regions of the world, where the memories held within each song bring me joy and, eventually, peace. These are sounds from diverse eras and places that might have never met in time, yet here they coexist in harmony.
Organic and electronic textures blend with emotional energy: they exalt intensity but also honor silence. Speed and stillness converge into a fluid harmony that invites reflection, memory, and breath.
Peace is not a moment,  it’s a continuous presence. It should be lived from every place, in every time, and remembered and desired always.

There's peace in the scene, peace in the relationship, peace in music, peace between countries, even peace in your rest, and it stays.
We'll find peace, always.

A tribute to the beautiful Adriatic sea and the mountain Biokovo in Croatia; jazzy, spacey, electronic, and ambient songs with subtle mystic undertones describe my weightless emotions when I am there - pure trance state.
A portal to another time; These songs, spanning the late 1960s to 1970s, echo an era when peace, protest, and reflection shaped music, something we could do with more of in this day and age.

Ablution redefines ambient music as a space for healing and resistance. Through a youthful lens, distorted voices, stillness, and triphop rhythms merge to reflect on peace as fragile and political, a moment to face yourself and the world with open, listening hands.

subtle.d:
DJ & Producer, B-Say has been a Subtle resident DJ for over 3 years.

His radio shows tend to focus on the 140 bass music scene and aims to showcase unreleased/forthcoming music from upcoming artists, as well as premiering his own unreleased material. 

More recently B-Say has ventured out from solely DJ'ing Dubstep, with his bi-monthly 'Dub & Steppers Show' which he uses to premier his own productions.

Slick is a London-based Producer and DJ combining the sounds of Grime and Drill.
Expect sets to span from sparse wave and weightless to classic NY and UK Drill, with everything in between
J:KENZO is a producer and record label owner (Artikal Music & Lion Charge) from the UK. Known for his minimalistic dark tribal sound in the both the dubstep and drum and bass scenes since 2006.
